Anthrax, Italy
--------------
Information received on [and dated] 16 Sep 2016 from Prof Dr Romano Marabelli, chief veterinary officer, secretary general, Ministry of Health, Rome, Italy

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 3 Sep 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 5 Sep 2016
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: July 2005
Manifestation of disease: sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Roma, Valmontone, Lazio
Date of start of the outbreak: 3 Sep 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Sheep / 680 / 2 / 2 / /
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Sheep / 0.3 / 0.3 / 100 / **
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter
**Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: disinfection/disinfestation; official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Experimental Zooprophilactic Institute-Foggia (national laboratory) / sheep / pathogenic agent isolation on culture / 5 Sep 2016 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak, to the immediate south east of Rome, can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above. - Mod.MHJ]

